</a>

An API wrapper for discord wich uses `async` and `await`.

# How to install

```shell
python3 -m pip install discord.wrapper
```

## Bot Example
```python
from discord import wrapper

bot = wrapper.Bot(command_prefix="!*", public_key = "Your Public Key", token="Your Bot Token")

@bot.command()
async def example(data):
    await data.send(data.message.author)

bot.run()
```

## Subclassed Bot

```python
from discord import wrapper

class MyBot(wrapper.Bot):
	def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
		super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)

bot = MyBot(command_prefix="!*", public_key = "public_key", token="Your Bot Token")

@bot.command()
async def example(data):
    await data.send(data.message.author)

bot.run()
```

